.TH "_shutdown" 9 "_shutdown" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
_shutdown \- shutdown an omap_hwmod
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" _shutdown
.BI "(struct omap_hwmod *oh "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "oh" 12
struct omap_hwmod *
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Shut down an omap_hwmod \fIoh\fP.  This should be called when the driver
used for the hwmod is removed or unloaded or if the driver is not
used by the system.  Returns -EINVAL if the hwmod is in the wrong
state or returns 0.
